---
import MainLayout from "../../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import MotuSidebar from '../../../components/MotuSidebar.astro';

const title = "Analog I/O & S/PDIF — UltraLite-mk3";
const description = "Analog and digital I/O overview.";
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description}>
    <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
      <div class="w-[250px] flex-shrink-0">
        <MotuSidebar />
      </div>
      <article class="prose max-w-none">
      <h1>Analog I/O & S/PDIF</h1>

      <h2>Complete I/O Map</h2>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Channel</th><th>Type</th><th>Connector</th><th>Location</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>In 1–2</td><td>Mic/Instrument</td><td>XLR/TRS combo</td><td>Front panel</td></tr>
          <tr><td>In 3–8</td><td>Line-level balanced</td><td>TRS ¼”</td><td>Rear panel</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Out 1–8</td><td>Line-level balanced</td><td>TRS ¼”</td><td>Rear panel</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Main Out L/R</td><td>Main stereo output</td><td>TRS ¼”</td><td>Rear panel</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Phones</td><td>Headphone stereo output</td><td>TRS ¼”</td><td>Front panel</td></tr>
          <tr><td>S/PDIF In</td><td>Stereo digital input</td><td>RCA</td><td>Rear panel</td></tr>
          <tr><td>S/PDIF Out</td><td>Stereo digital output</td><td>RCA</td><td>Rear panel</td></tr>
          <tr><td>MIDI In</td><td>MIDI receive</td><td>5-pin DIN</td><td>Rear panel</td></tr>
          <tr><td>MIDI Out</td><td>MIDI transmit</td><td>5-pin DIN</td><td>Rear panel</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Output Assignments in This Studio</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Main Out L/R → Yamaha HS7:</strong> balanced TRS cables from MOTU Main Outputs to HS7 L/R inputs. Use TRS-to-TRS if both connectors are TRS; TRS-to-XLR if the HS7 uses XLR inputs.</li>
        <li><strong>Phones → Headphones:</strong> connect studio or tracking headphones to the front-panel PHONES jack for cue monitoring during recording.</li>
        <li><strong>S/PDIF:</strong> currently reserved for future expansion (e.g., a hardware reverb unit, ADAT expander, or outboard S/PDIF converter).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Balanced vs Unbalanced Connections</h2>
      <p>Always use balanced TRS cables between the MOTU and HS7 monitors. Balanced connections cancel out electromagnetic interference (hum from power supplies, USB cables) because both signal wires carry identical signals — one inverted. At the receiving end, the inverting leg is flipped back and the noise cancels. This is especially important in a studio with multiple USB devices and switching power supplies nearby.</p>

      <img src="https://cdn-data.motu.com/site/images/ultralite-mk3/web1-5/ultralite-mk3-large-front.jpg" alt="UltraLite-mk3 front" class="w-full rounded" />
    </article>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
